{
  "abstract": "The soil and water conservation is one of the most important components of\r\nintegrated watershed program. Earlier in soil and water conservation programs,\r\ne$orts were concentrated on construction of various types of bunds across the\r\nslope. This helped in controlling erosion and reducing soil loss rather than increasing\r\ncrop yields through additional moisture conservation. Current emphasis is more\r\non improving moisture through various %eld- and community-based moisture\r\nconservation practices. This paper discusses the key %ndings from the various\r\nwatershed programs and research stations on %eld- and community-based soil\r\nand water conservation interventions that were found promising for improving\r\nproductivity and reducing land degradation in di$erent regions of India.",
